    • Enum Constant Detail

      • CANCELLED

        public static final CompletionReason CANCELLED
        Cancelled before nozzle lift. Authorise or Reserve was cancelled.

      • NORMAL

        public static final CompletionReason NORMAL
        Normal delivery. This includes deliveries that stopped at or under the authorised limit.

      • NOT_COMPLETE

        public static final CompletionReason NOT_COMPLETE
        Transaction is in progress (e.g. reserved, authorised or delivering) and not yet complete

      • OFFLINE

        public static final CompletionReason OFFLINE
        The Transaction was created because offline deliveries where detected from the dispenser electronic totals.

      • STOPPED_BY_CLIENT

        public static final CompletionReason STOPPED_BY_CLIENT
        Fuel Transaction was stopped by a Client during delivery

      • STOPPED_BY_ERROR

        public static final CompletionReason STOPPED_BY_ERROR
        Fuel Transaction was stopped due to an error.

      • STOPPED_BY_LIMIT

        public static final CompletionReason STOPPED_BY_LIMIT
        Pump Server will monitor the running totals of a transaction which has an Authorisation limit set. If it finds the limit is being exceeded it will try and stop the delivery and complete the transaction with this completion reason. Not all pump types support running totals.

      • TIMEOUT

        public static final CompletionReason TIMEOUT
        Timeout before nozzle lift. The time limit for a Authorise or Reserve expired.

      • ZERO

        public static final CompletionReason ZERO
        Fuel Transaction which was authorised but no fuel was delivered.
